H0.text: Clone is a term in biotechnology that refers to a genetically exact copy of an organism.

H1.text: Adult is the term in biotechnology that refers to a genetically exact copy of an organism.

H2.text: Male is the term in biotechnology that means a genetically exact copy of an organism.

H3.text: Phenotype is the term in biotechnology that means a genetically exact copy of an organism.

A4.text: Cloning, the production of any organism whose genetic information is identical to that of a parent organism from which it was created.

A5.text: Clone (cell biology), a group of identical cells that share a common ancestry.
